H3.text: Vendredi is French for which day of the week. TGIFF

A4.text: The word for Friday in most Romance languages is derived from Latin dies Veneris or 'day of Venus', such as vendredi in French.

A5.text: vendredi in French is derived from Latin dies Veneris, meaning 'day of Venus', which corresponds to Friday.
